  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Impler, JarImpler
    public class Implementor
extends Object
implements JarImpler
    Realisation of interface JarImpler Create implementation of given class or interface method Impler.implement(Class, Path) Produces .jar file implementing class or interface JarImpler.implementJar(Class, Path) Create generation of the interfaces and classes

      • isSupportedToken

        private void isSupportedToken​(Class<?> token)
                       throws ImplerException
        Check token:
        • token is not Enum and Class.isEnum() == false
        • token is not array Class.isArray()== false
        • token is not primitive Class.isPrimitive()== false
        • token is not final
        • token is not private
        Parameters:
        token - type token
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if token is illegal for implementing.
